Single Media View

Allow user to comment on uploaded media
This will display the comment form and comment listing on single media pages as well as inside lightbox (if lightbox is enabled).
Enable view count
You may want to show total views of the media to users.

Media Likes

Enable likes for media
Enabling this setting will add like feature for media.
Likes page in Media tab
Add a separate "Likes" page under the "Media" tab in every user's profile that will display any media that the user has liked.
Likes in media comments
Add a "Like" button under every media comment in lightbox & single page.

rating for media

Enable 5 star rating for media
Allow user to rate media.
Enable 5 star rating for albums
Allow user to rate albums.

Gallery Media Search

Enable gallery media search
This will enable the search box in gallery page.

List Media View

Use lightbox to display media
View single media in facebook style lightbox.
Number of media per page
Number of media items you want to show per page on front end.
Media display pagination option
Choose whether you want the load more button or pagination buttons.

Masonry View

Enable Masonry Cascading grid layout
If you enable masonry view, it is advisable to regenerate thumbnail for masonry view.

You might need to change thumbnail size and uncheck the crop box for thumbnails.

To set gallery for fixed width, set image height to 0 and width as per your requirement and vice-versa.

Enable Masonry Cascading grid layout for activity
If you enable masonry view, it is advisable to regenerate thumbnail for masonry view.

Direct Upload

Enable Direct Upload
Uploading media directly as soon as it gets selected.

Miscellaneous

Display documents and other files in table style (only for Document and Others tab)
In Document and Others tab, all files can be displayed in tabular format.
Enable Google Docs for documents and files.
In lightbox media view, display the docs, pdf, excel and other office documents in Google Docs.
Display Tags for audio ( mp3 ) files.
Enabling this option,will display the audio tags embedded inside audio( mp3 ) files. The tags are also editable.
Display music in playlist style (only for music tab)
On music tab, rather than opening lightbox/single-page and listening to songs one-by-one, all songs can be played in playlist style.

Attachment Support For WordPress Comments

Enable attachments in comments
Option to upload/attach media/files to WordPress comments using comment form on front-end
Enable for non-logged in users also
It is NOT recommended to use this option. This will allow non-logged in user to upload files using comment form. If you use this option, make sure you haven't enabled any sensitive file type extension.
Display attachments in comments as
Control how you want to display uploaded media files in comment listing

Sitewide Gallery Section

Enable sitewide gallery section
This will enable sitewide gallery feature. Gallery is collection of albums and can be manage from WordPress dashboard, like a custom post type.
Slug for sitewide gallery section
It is not recommended to change this setting again and again. This will be act as a base for all albums created from dashboard.

You can manage sitewide galleries from here.

Attachment Support for bbPress

Enable attachments in topic/reply
Option to upload/attach media/files to bbPress topic/reply on front-end.
Enable for non-logged in users also
It is NOT recommended to use this option. This will allow non-logged in user to upload files using topic/reply form. If you use this option, make sure you haven't enabled any sensitive file type extension.
Display attachments in topic/reply as
Control how you want to display uploaded/attached media files in reply.

You can manage file types/extension from here

Configuration

The following PHP constants can be defined in your wp-config.php file in order to control the behavior of Query Monitor:

QM_DARK_MODE
Enable dark mode for Query Monitor's interface.
Default value: false
QM_DB_EXPENSIVE
If an individual database query takes longer than this time to execute, it's considered "slow" and triggers a warning.
Default value: 0.05
QM_DISABLED
Disable Query Monitor entirely.
Default value: false
QM_DISABLE_ERROR_HANDLER
Disable the handling of PHP errors.
Default value: false
QM_ENABLE_CAPS_PANEL
Enable the Capability Checks panel.
Default value: false
QM_HIDE_CORE_ACTIONS
Hide WordPress core on the Hooks & Actions panel.
Default value: false
QM_HIDE_SELF
Hide Query Monitor itself from various panels.
Default value: false
QM_NO_JQUERY
Don't specify jQuery as a dependency of Query Monitor. If jQuery isn't enqueued then Query Monitor will still operate, but with some reduced functionality.
Default value: false
QM_SHOW_ALL_HOOKS
In the Hooks & Actions panel, show every hook that has an action or filter attached (instead of every action hook that fired during the request).
Default value: false
